          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 6 1/4 in. by 4 1/4, consisting of 108 leaves, some
                                    of which are much stained and torn, especially foll.
              24, 69, 74, 85, 86, 89, and 93—102. The quires, signed with letters, were
                                    at least 18 in number. The first two are now missing, and leaves
                                    are wanting after foll. 60, 68, 76, 82, 84, 85, 86, 92,
                                       100, and 108. The number of
                                    lines in each page varies from 13 to 22.</p>
